<circuit>
  <version>2</version>
  <attributes>
    <entry>
      <string>romContent</string>
      <romList>
        <roms/>
      </romList>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <string>preloadProgram</string>
      <boolean>true</boolean>
    </entry>
    <entry>
      <string>preloadProgramFile</string>
      <file>/Users/me/Desktop/PROJECT/main.bin</file>
    </entry>
  </attributes>
  <visualElements>
    <visualElement>
      <elementName>Text</elementName>
      <elementAttributes>
        <entry>
          <string>Description</string>
          <string>NEXT, NEED LOAD AND STORE,
Address comes from ALU output
which goes to memory via see-thru latch
 latch,which goes out to memory for 
loading and storing.  reads 32-word
and stores in rd.   Need to figure out a good
approach to read and write to memory 
with Digital and load it at start up.
We need to arbitrate use of memory 
between load/store and fetching instruction.</string>
        </entry>
      </elementAttributes>
      <pos x="440" y="680"/>
    </visualElement>
    <visualElement>
      <elementName>Text</elementName>
      <elementAttributes>
        <entry>
          <string>Description</string>
          <string>PCU (Program Control Unit, 
PC = PC + 4, or PC = PC += SBimm32
or PC = ALU out or PC += sgn_ext-imm32
for FMT U, and UJ

Need to figure out a way to load memory
with instructions, ideally from RARS.
Check out how MARS does it for MIPS.</string>
        </entry>
      </elementAttributes>
      <pos x="440" y="380"/>
    </visualElement>
    <visualElement>
      <elementName>Text</elementName>
      <elementAttributes>
        <entry>
          <string>Description</string>
          <string>Here we are trying to make this circuit hierarchical
    RV5-REGS contains register bank related hw.
    RV5-ALU contains ALU related hw
    RV5-INSTR-DECODE contains Instruction Reg, and all needed decodes
          decoder for immediate sel
    RV5-IMM is a combinatorial that extracts the needed immediates, 
           and provides the sign-extended 32-bit value thru a MUX.
    RV5-PCU needs some fixes.
           increments the PC and allows Jumps, and provides next PC for JAL save of PC.

See examples in Digital in particular processors as to how 
to do this.  

TODO: 
1st. Add a test to each element in the hierarchy.
2nd Resize boxes with appropriate SVG for readable packages w. appropriate signals.

We need to:
    RV5-INSTR-DECODE: Decodes the instruction set and provides control signals, and FMT
         decode for immediate select has been completed.
    Implement:
         RV5-LOAD-STORE: Provides Load and Store
         RV5-MEMORY: Include ROM and RAM.
         RV5-IO: Provides a mean to read a program, communicate with a terminal (keyboard/display)

         Create a ROM/RAM  bootstrap
              that loads a program.

Note: Assembler test programs can be found at:   
   https://github.com/riscv-software-src/riscv-tests</string>
        </entry>
      </elementAttributes>
      <pos x="340" y="1020"/>
    </visualElement>
